def greet():
    return "Good day to you!"

print(greet())
```

In this example, the `@hello_world()` decorator is applied to the `greet()` function. The `hello_world()` function returns a new function that, when called, returns the string "Hello, World!". So, when you call `greet()`, it will return "Hello, World!".

